  "text": "These vibrations transmit themselves through the body, causing a notable stimulation of sensorial receptors, principally the neuromuscular spindles. Recent studies have demonstrated that brief exposures to this type of treatment causes an acute increase in the muscular capacity of the subject, in both the upper [CITATION_1] and lower [CITATION_2] extremities. It has also been observed to produce an increase in the consumption of oxygen (O 2 ), of cardiac frequency (FC) and of the subjective perception of strength (RPE), similar to that produced with moderate resistance training [CITATION_3] .",
